Brute Force: T.C. - O(N^2) - replace takes O(n) , S.C. - O(N) - string is mutuable, new string created (for replacement)
Approach : Everytime you see (), you remove it from the string, if the whole string is empty at the end, solution
is true

class Solution:
    def isValid(self, s: str) -> bool:
        while '()' in s or '[]' in s or '{}' in s:
            s = s.replace('()','')
            s = s.replace('[]','')
            s = s.replace('{}','')
        return s == ''


Optimal : T.C. - O(N) , S.C. - O(N)
Approach: Put the close brackets in dic, till any of the close brackets are found, we append the rest in the stack
when we find the close bracket in the string and the value pair of dictionary is checked, then pop if found.
That way, equal no of brackets are cut and order is also followed.

class Solution:
    def isValid(self, s: str) -> bool:
         stack = []
         openToClose = {")" : "(", "]" : "[" , "}" : "{"}

         for c in s:
            if c in openToClose:
                if stack and stack[-1] == openToClose[c]:
                    stack.pop()
                else:
                    return False
            else:
                stack.append(c)
         return True if not stack else False
